TransactionStateContext.Withdraw State: When the owner withdraws the entire balance of the contract through the withdraw function.
TransactionStateContext.Command Execution State: When the owner uses the Command function to execute arbitrary commands with the given data.
TransactionStateContext.Multiplication State: When users interact with the multiplicate function, potentially transferring funds to an address.

ExternalInteractions.Withdrawal: Transfers all contract funds to the owner's address.
ExternalInteractions.Command Execution: Performs a low-level call to another address with arbitrary data, specified by the owner.
ExternalInteractions.Multiplication: Transfers the contract balance and sent value to a specified address if msg.value is greater than or equal to the contract balance.
